1. Explain about Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps is a Microsoft low-code/no-code platform, that allows we can quickly build custom business applications without need any coding skills.
ğŸ‘‰ It supports creating an apps with drag-and-drop controls, connecting to different data sources like SharePoint, Dataverse, and more.

ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps supports building an apps mainly two types:
1. Canvas Apps.
2. Model-Driven Apps.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ğŸ”¹ Key features of Power Apps (based on my experience):
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
1. Low-code development             ---> I build apps quickly using drag-and-drop conrols without need any coding skills.
2. Canvas and Model-Driven apps     ---> I choose based on UI needs or data focus.
3. Multiple data connections        ---> I connect apps easily to SharePoint, Dataverse, SQL, Excel, etc.
4. Integration with PowerAutomate   ---> I automate workflows from inside the app itself.
5. Security and permissions         ---> I manage user access through Dataverse security roles.
6. Responsive design                ---> Especially with Model-Driven apps, it adjusts automatically for mobile and Desktop.
7. Reusable components              ---> I create custom components to maintain consistency across apps.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Difference between Canvas App and Model-Driven App?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ In Canvas Apps, gives full control over the appâ€™s design and layout â€” like drag and drop controls wherever we want.
ğŸ‘‰ I use Canvas Apps when I need a highly customized UI part, like building forms, designing the galleries from scratch.

ğŸ‘‰ In Model-Driven Apps, the design is based on data structure (tables, relationships) â€” so layout is automatically generated by Power Apps.
ğŸ‘‰ I prefer Model-Driven Apps for complex business processes where we already have structured data in Dataverse, like (eg, Customer Service apps). 
