5. What are Components in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Components are reusable building blocks â€” like custom controls that I can create once and use across multiple screens or apps.
For example:
ğŸ‘‰ I build a custom header or navigation menu as a component and reuse it on every screen.
ğŸ‘‰ Suppose in this way, if I need to make any changes, I can only update the component, and it automatically reflects across all screens.
ğŸ‘‰ It saves a lot of time because I donâ€™t have to copy-paste the same design on every screen.

ğŸ”¹ I can pass data into components using input and output properties.
1. Input properties let me send data into the component, like passing a userâ€™s name or a color choice to customize it.
2. Output properties are used to send data back or trigger actions from the component, like when a button inside it is clicked. 

Example:
ğŸ‘‰ In my project, I created a header component with dynamic titles and used it on 10+ screens, making the app faster to update and manage.
