16. How do you create a Responsive Design in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Responsive design in Power Apps means building apps that automatically adapt their layout and controls to fit different screen sizes,
    â€” desktop, tablet, or mobile.
ğŸ‘‰ To create a responsive Design, I use container controls like vertical and horizontal containers based on the appâ€™s needs.
ğŸ‘‰ These containers automatically arrange the elements inside them based on the screen size.
ğŸ‘‰ Instead of fixing each controlâ€™s size and position, I use formulas to adjust width and height relative to the screen.

For Example:
ğŸ‘‰ Uisng relative properities like "parent.width and parent.height" it helps to adjust their sizes and positions dynamically.
