17. What are the Role-Based Security in Power Apps. How do you manage them?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Role-Based Security controls define the what users can see and do in Power Apps and Dataverse based on their assigned roles (like Admin, Manager, Employee).
ğŸ‘‰ In Dataverse, I assign security roles directly to users or teams.
ğŸ‘‰ Each role defines specific permissions (like Read, Write, Delete) on tables, forms, apps, or even specific records.
ğŸ‘‰ This ensures that sensitive data and critical actions are accessible only to authorized users.

Example:
ğŸ‘‰ In my recent project, Managers had access to update employee data, while Employees could only view their own profile.
