18. Solutions in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Solutions are containers used to package, manage, and deploy Power Platform components like Power Apps, Power Automate flows, tables and other components together.
ğŸ‘‰ During development, I use Unmanaged Solutions â€” these allow easy editing and collaboration.
ğŸ‘‰ Once the app is tested and finalized, I export it as a Managed Solution for the Production environment.
    which are read-only to ensure stability and controlled updates.
ğŸ‘‰ Solutions help me easily move apps between different environments (like Dev â” QA â” Prod) without missing any pieces.

ğŸ”¹ Why Solutions are important (Real-world value):
ğŸ”„ ALM (Application Lifecycle Management): Ideal for moving apps from Dev â†’ Test â†’ Prod.
â™»ï¸ Supports version control and rollback.
ğŸ”„ Easily export/import entire apps + data schema + logic.

Example:
ğŸ‘‰ In one project, I built an onboarding app inside a Solution, and then exported it from Dev and imported it into the QA and Production environments smoothly.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

19. How do you use Power Apps in implement conditional formatting in your app?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Conditional formatting in Power Apps mainly through formulas on properties like Color, Fill, or Visible.
ğŸ‘‰ Instead of hardcoding styles, I apply logic using If statements or Switch based on field values or user roles.

âœ… Common use cases:
1. Change label or text color based on status: Color = If(ThisItem.Status = "Completed", Green, Red)
2. Highlight cards or controls when a condition is met: Fill = If(ThisItem.Score < 50, RGBA(255,0,0,0.1), White)
3. Show/hide fields depending on user role: Visible = If(User().Email = "admin@domain.com", true, false)
4. Disable controls until a required field is filled: DisplayMode = If(IsBlank(DataCardValue1.Text), DisplayMode.Disabled, DisplayMode.Edit)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

20. Difference between configuration and customization?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Configuration means  using built-in settings to make the system work how you want, without any coding. 
    Like changing forms, adding fields, or creating filters.

ğŸ‘‰ Customization means writing code or building new features to change how the system works, 
    like adding custom logic or integrating with other apps.

ğŸ‘‰ So, configuration is easier and faster, and customization is for when you need something more advanced.







